lead_paragraph: A Washington correspondent of The Courier and Enquirer has the following remarks in regard to the rumored existence of a treaty between England, Spain, and the United States, guaranteeing the preservation of Cuba to Spain: You have no doubt seen what has been reiterated in the public press, about a correspondence in the archives of the State Department,
